          <p class="font-sora text-stone-600 leading-relaxed mb-4">A lot of bird listings describe what an African Grey is like in year one, maybe two. The honest answer is that a Congo grey changes across decades. The bird Roys is at 4 months is different from who he will be at 5 years, and different again at 15. A Congo's personality deepens, not flattens. He gets more opinionated, more expressive, and if well-handled, more bonded over time.</p>

