        </li>
        <li class="flex gap-3">
          <span style="color:#2D6A4F;font-weight:700;flex-shrink:0;">✔</span>
          <span class="font-sora text-stone-600 text-sm"><strong class="text-logo-dark">Limited fruit</strong> — apple, papaya, mango in small pieces. High sugar, so keep it occasional and use it for training rewards rather than a meal component.</span>
        </li>
        <li class="flex gap-3">
          <span style="color:#2D6A4F;font-weight:700;flex-shrink:0;">✔</span>
          <span class="font-sora text-stone-600 text-sm"><strong class="text-logo-dark">Calcium support + UV-B light</strong> — Greys are specifically prone to hypocalcemia. We raise our birds with full-spectrum UV-B lighting and vitamin D3 supplementation so they can actually absorb the calcium in their diet.</span>
